    <br/>

    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>The date of last contact from OpenClinica is the last known alive status from any source, including outside of the EMR or health system contact - could be a variety of sources and is pre-populated from registry. This is a true vital status date and indicator - it may sometimes be the same as the last health system contact, but is NOT collected as such.</p>

<p>We have asked abstraction to create a new variable to represent the true last health system contact to use as the appropriate censor point for a patient’s record for clinical endpoints (<a href="https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/EDF-56" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/EDF-56</a> ). </p>



<p>This ticket is to implement as a data element in the ADS  and to use in <a href="https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/ADS-371" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://n-power.atlassian.net/browse/ADS-371</a> </p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <br/>

